            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Actually with `'balloonevalterm'` this happens in Vim running in GNOME Terminal as well:\n```vim\nlet g:ev = 0\nfunc MouseMove()\n  let mp = getmousepos()\n  let g:ev += 1\n  echomsg $'Move {g:ev} line {mp.screenrow}, col {mp.screencol}'\nendfunc\nnnoremap <MouseMove> <Cmd>call MouseMove()<CR>\nif exists('+balloonevalterm')\n  set balloonevalterm\nendif\nif exists('+mousemoveevent')\n  set mousemoveevent\nendif\n```\n\nI've not found another terminal emulator that exhibits this behavior, but if GNOME Terminal doesn't change this, maybe something should still be done.",
