            "body": "Doh! Right, I was comparing apples and oranges (nvim-terminal vs vim-gui). (and what's with needing balloonevalterm for plain vim and not gvim? Sigh.)\n\n> I've not found another terminal emulator that exhibits this behavior, but if GNOME Terminal doesn't change this, \n> maybe something should still be done.\n\nAt least it's very cheap to work around.\n\nAre there any requirements/expectations for the gui's in this area? \n\n-----\n\nBTW, there's some kind of issue with `key_name_entry` table, `get_special_key_name()` and K_MOUSEMOVE. A mouse move comes in as `0xffff9803` but K_MOUSEMOVE is `0xffff9b03` and so in the log there's `DBG ... state_enter:100: input: <t_?g>`\n\nQuick and dirty, the following gets the key to display correctly in the log.\n```\n  //{ K_MOUSEMOVE,       \"MouseMove\" },\n  { 0xffff9803,       \"MouseMove\" },\n```",
